15. Pulso Vindice. Julius Vindex, propraetor of Gaul, rose against Nero, having first offered the empire to Galba. Verginius commanding in upper Germany marched against the insurgente, and his army engaged and defeated them in spite of an agreement which is said to have been come to between the generals on either side.

16. Adseruit nora sibi. He proved his disinterestedness by refusing the empire which was offered to him. See on Ep. 16. 4.

17. Parata oblivio: see on Ep. 25. 30.
